Documentation: How to Run Django + YOLOv5 Application Using Docker

This guide explains how to build and run a Django application that uses YOLOv5
Ultralytics for image detection inside a Docker container.


Make sure you have the following installed:

1. Prerequisites
Docker
Check using:
    docker --version
    
2. Project Structure

Your Django project folder should look like this:
myproject/
│── manage.py
│── Dockerfile
│── app/ (your Django app)
│── myproject/ (settings folder)
│── requirements.txt (optional)

3. Dockerfile Explanation

Here is the Dockerfile being used:
      Dockerfile
  
4.Build the Docker Image

Navigate to your project directory:
    cd /path/to/myproject
    docker build -t my-django-yolov5 .    #Build the Docker image
This downloads Python, installs all dependencies, and prepares YOLO + Django.

5.Run the Docker Container

Run your Django + YOLOv5 app:
     docker run -p 8000:8000 my-django-yolov5
     
6. Access the Application

Open a browser and go to:
	http://0.0.0.0:8000









